Assignment Files: 
       lab8_1\BinaraySearchTree.java
       lab8_1\HeghtEstimator.java

Optional File: 
	lab8_1\BinarySearchTreeTest.java  (to the test the height method)


compile: 

$ javac BinaraySearchTree.java
$ javac HeghtEstimator.java


Run:

$ java HeghtEstimator

Results:

* The average height of a BinarySearchTree with 10 elements is 5.65

* Values of ratio for 5 times with n = 1000, 2000, 4000, 8000, and 16000 

 ------------------------------------------------------------------
|            |        value of ration for each run                 |
 ------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| value of n |  1st-run     2nd run    3rd-run    4th-run  5th-run | 
 ------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| 1000       |   2.2        2.2         2.2        2.2       2.2   |
| 2000       |   2.2        2.3         2.2        2.2	     2.2   |
| 4000       |   2.2        2.3         2.3        2.3       2.3   |
| 8000       |   2.3        2.3         2.3        2.3       2.3   |
| 16000      |   2.3        2.3         2.3        2.4       2.3   |
